openclaw agent --agent trading --thinking off --json --message 'Run one trading review using SOUL.md. Start with reconcile_approvals, then call get_trading_state. If macro_state.stale=true, refresh it once with update_macro_state. Then call get_review_universe and process every returned symbol exactly once. For each symbol, call get_market_data with compact=true to confirm source and freshness, then call calculate_indicator using symbol/market/interval/lookback so the tool fetches full data internally instead of copying long candle arrays through the chat context. Validate the final signal with generate_signal, write one decision log entry per symbol, and only call check_risk or place_order when the rules allow it. If execution_allowed=false for a symbol, you may analyze it but must not place a real order. Any real order must go through human approval.'
